                    },
                    "companyName": "Cornell Institute for Climate Smart Solutions"
                },
                {
                    "title": "Associate Dean, Director",
                    "description": "The College of Agriculture and Life Sciences (CALS) at Cornell University is one of the premier college’s of agriculture and related sciences in the world. The Associate Dean is an influential member of the College leadership team and contributes to strategic planning, helps determine the allocation of resources, and provides leadership on diverse college initiatives all in support of teaching, research and extension. The Cornell University Agricultural Experiment Station (CUAES), which was established in 1888, is one of a national system of federally designated Experiment Stations located in every state. As Director, i was responsible for the $5.2 million annual allocation of funds to CUAES of which ∼$4 million was used to support research conducted by faculty in the Colleges of Agriculture and Life Sciences, Human Ecology, and Veterinary Medicine. I also oversaw management of seven research and educational farms located across New York State, several thousand acres of forested properties, four acres of greenhouses, 150 environmentally controlled plant growth chambers and 50 personnel.",
